sec.title: Ethics approval and consent to participate
sec.p: The different chemotypes of Cinnamomum camphora used in this study was produced by Jiangxi Academy of Forestry in Nanchang and Nanjing Forestry University in Nanjing, China. C. camphora was widely cultivated in the south of China. All of voucher specimens were deposited in the Herbarium of Jiangxi Academy of Forestry and Nanjing Forestry University. Experimental research on the different chemotypes of C. camphora, including collection of this plant material, complies with institutional, national and international guidelines.
